#if soper
Command provided by: hostserv/disable
#endif
Help for DISABLE:

Permanently deactivates and removes your vhost.  After using
this command, your real hostname will be visible in /whois.
This action is irreversible, unless you ask network staff to
set it again.

If you only want to turn it off temporarily, use the OFF command.

Syntax: DISABLE

Examples:
    /msg &nick& DISABLE